{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"587785a0-da3a-4b33-8bc9-71cf3501cd0a","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic Task MyTunitTest() => Task.CompletedTask;\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as \"skipped\" (not failed) in test results, with the reason visible in the output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c043fb01-34cd-4e53-b2e9-f6de57835018","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct attributes to skip tests with a reason message in each of the four test frameworks: MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. This is a knowledge question about .NET test frameworks. Let me provide the answer directly since I know this well.","outputTokens":349,"requestId":"BC26:15A91A:2693DD:2CDF22:69FA93D0"},"id":"7902e116-f158-48bf-9e9b-79201ba7e0a2","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:05:27.750Z","parentId":"b19c2bfd-4dc3-4ccd-bdc3-0cd89079776e"}
